- VSCode Version:
1.8.0-insider (tested for 1.7, too)
- OS Version:
Windows 10

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Created following CompletionItemProvider:

```
export class ManifestCompletionItemProvider implements vscode.CompletionItemProvider {
    public provideCompletionItems(document: vscode.TextDocument, position: vscode.Position, token: vscode.CancellationToken): Thenable<vscode.CompletionItem[]> | vscode.CompletionItem[]  {
		let line = document.lineAt(position);
		let matches = line.text.match(/"(.*)"\s*:\s*(.*)\s*[,]?\s*/)
		if(!matches)
			return [];
		
		let key = matches[1];
		let value = matches[2];
		let val;

		switch (key) {
			case "target":
				console.log("Target triggered");
				let targets: string[];
				try {
					let targets = getTargets(JSON.parse(document.getText()));
				} catch (error) {
					return [];
				}

				if(!targets)
					return [];
				value = value.match(/"(.*)"/)[1];

				if(!value) {
					val = enumerable.asEnumerable(targets).Select(x => {
						let item = new vscode.CompletionItem(x, vscode.CompletionItemKind.Text);
						item.insertText = "\""+x+"\"";
						return item;
					}).ToArray(); 
					return val;
				}
				return enumerable.asEnumerable(targets).Where(x => x.toLowerCase().startsWith(value.toLowerCase())).Select(x => {
						let item = new vscode.CompletionItem(x, vscode.CompletionItemKind.Text);
						item.insertText = "\""+x+"\"";
						return item;
					}).ToArray();
			default:
				return [];
		}
    }
}
```

2. I added it to the json language server completion providers:

```
const ui5_manifest: vscode.DocumentFilter = { language: "json", scheme: 'file', pattern: "**/manifest.json"};
context.subscriptions.push(vscode.languages.registerCompletionItemProvider(ui5_manifest, new ManifestCompletionItemProvider));
```

3. When I trigger it by changing pressing ctrl+space my breakpoint gets hit, my method runs properly and returns the array of `CompletionItem`s. For the first time (sometimes) the results show up, but vanish immediately after that and never show up again.

I can trigger the method multiple times and it always returns that array, but no code completion.

Is there any way to convince the JSON Completion to show my results, too?

The document filter should get a high priority, as I filled in all props.

And why is it crashing the whole list. There should be the completion items from the JSON language server?
